- And Veronica.
- The ballerina, right?

87
00:05:17,364 --> 00:05:20,141
Do you have a gun like my mom?

88
00:05:20,141 --> 00:05:24,603
- I do. Yeah.
- Anyway. The library.

89
00:05:24,603 --> 00:05:27,231
See you tonight.

90
00:05:31,476 --> 00:05:33,489
Family drama?

91
00:05:34,530 --> 00:05:38,580
There's this guy at Finley park,
where she likes to play.

92
00:05:38,580 --> 00:05:40,168
He up to something?

93
00:05:40,168 --> 00:05:43,606
I don't know.
He just sits there, reading.

94
00:05:43,606 --> 00:05:46,326
But you don't like how he looks.

95
00:05:46,326 --> 00:05:48,818
He doesn't have a kid there.

96
00:05:48,818 --> 00:05:51,285
Just bothers me.

97
00:05:51,701 --> 00:05:54,860
- Want me to check him out?
- You mind?

98
00:05:54,860 --> 00:05:56,910
Nah.

99
00:05:59,688 --> 00:06:03,632
Grant Bowen, 40,
ER doc at st. Walter's.

100
00:06:03,632 --> 00:06:06,710
Theory in '84 was a mugging gone wrong.

101
00:06:06,710 --> 00:06:09,185
Killed on his way home after his shift.

102
00:06:09,185 --> 00:06:12,971
- St. Walt's is in a rough part of town.
- Shot with a 38.

103
00:06:12,971 --> 00:06:16,467
The slug was recovered,
weapon was never found.

104
00:06:16,467 --> 00:06:19,515
Homeless guy they arrested
had on the doc's top-siders.

105
00:06:19,515 --> 00:06:21,043
But he could've taken them
after the doc was killed.

106
00:06:21,043 --> 00:06:23,586
Jury didn't think so.
Guy was convicted.

107
00:06:23,586 --> 00:06:25,254
Died in jail two months later.

108
00:06:25,254 --> 00:06:29,269
The only physical evidence was a red, 
heart-shaped sticker found by the doc's body.

109
00:06:29,269 --> 00:06:33,293
- Valentine's heart?
- Murder was in August, not February.

110
00:06:33,293 --> 00:06:36,966
According to this witness,
doc was chatting it up with the doer.

111
00:06:36,966 --> 00:06:40,849
- Who had a hospital baseball cap.
- Huh, something personal.

112
00:06:40,849 --> 00:06:44,411
Will's on his way to Drexel.
Widow's an English professor there.

113
00:06:44,411 --> 00:06:46,288
You could still catch up
with him if you hurry.

114
00:06:46,288 --> 00:06:49,406
- He's off desk duty?
- Boss brokered a deal.

115
00:06:49,406 --> 00:06:53,355
I had to. The man was playing
with a flying squirrel.

116
00:06:55,344 --> 00:06:57,510
I met Grant when he was a resident.

117
00:06:57,510 --> 00:07:01,108
Broke my ankle ice-skating,
he put on the cast.

118
00:07:01,108 --> 00:07:02,978
And the rest is history?

119
00:07:02,978 --> 00:07:04,595
And we were such opposites.

120
00:07:04,595 --> 00:07:06,100
Opposites how?

121
00:07:06,100 --> 00:07:08,269
I come from a family of academics.

122
00:07:08,269 --> 00:07:11,240
Grant was a steel worker's son.

123
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:13,911
He sure made good,
becoming a doctor.

124
00:07:13,911 --> 00:07:16,130
And he could've worked anywhere,

125
00:07:16,130 --> 00:07:18,089
but he wanted to give back.

126
00:07:18,089 --> 00:07:19,571
That's why st. Walter's.

127
00:07:19,571 --> 00:07:24,290
We have new information that your husband 
may have been shot by someone he knew, Anne.

128
00:07:24,290 --> 00:07:29,770
- A white guy, possibly from the hospital.
- Oh, my god.

129
00:07:29,770 --> 00:07:33,625
Anyone that fits that description
that may have wanted to hurt grant?

130
00:07:33,625 --> 00:07:35,190
Maybe.

131
00:07:35,190 --> 00:07:37,684
- Another doctor in the ER.
- What's his name?

132
00:07:37,684 --> 00:07:40,230
- Seth Garvey.
- They didn't get along?

133
00:07:40,230 --> 00:07:44,010
They did, but Seth envied Grant.

134
00:07:44,010 --> 00:07:46,236
- Professionally?
- For starters.

135
00:07:46,236 --> 00:07:52,268
We were at a medical convention in Atlantic
city eight months before Grant died.

136
00:07:56,659 --> 00:07:58,639
- Here comes the river.
- What's that?

137
00:07:58,639 --> 00:08:00,278
Last common card dealt.
It's called the river

138
00:08:00,278 --> 00:08:01,827
'cause your hand's fate depends on it.

139
00:08:01,827 --> 00:08:05,001
- Very existential.
- I love that.

140
00:08:05,001 --> 00:08:06,765
- Yes! Yes!
- Damn!

141
00:08:06,765 --> 00:08:08,352
Fate is with me.

142
00:08:08,352 --> 00:08:12,152
Well, I'm in the middle of a great book 
about sir Francis Bacon, so I'm going up.

143
00:08:12,152 --> 00:08:14,568
- Coming?
- Another half an hour.

144
00:08:14,568 --> 00:08:16,528
Come here.

145
00:08:17,546 --> 00:08:19,808
You got beginner's luck
like I've never seen.

146
00:08:19,808 --> 00:08:25,472
Yep, my father used to say
better to be lucky than smart.

147
00:08:25,948 --> 00:08:27,391
Adios, boys.

148
00:08:27,391 --> 00:08:29,081
Hey, let me walk you up, Anne.

149
00:08:29,081 --> 00:08:31,050
A lot of shady characters about.

150
00:08:31,050 --> 00:08:33,732
Podiatrists and the like.

151
00:08:34,446 --> 00:08:36,773
You know, I never heard grant
mention his dad before.

152
00:08:36,773 --> 00:08:39,164
- Usually doesn't.
- Why's that?

153
00:08:39,164 --> 00:08:40,986
He was a drunk. Deadbeat.

154
00:08:40,986 --> 00:08:42,779
And Grant's perfect.

155
00:08:42,779 --> 00:08:45,046
Overcompensating I guess.

156
00:08:45,046 --> 00:08:47,504
He's not perfect.

157
00:08:47,975 --> 00:08:49,253
But almost.

158
00:08:49,253 --> 00:08:51,838
Must be fun to live with.

159
00:08:51,838 --> 00:08:55,669
So where to?

160
00:08:55,669 --> 00:08:58,085
What?

161
00:08:58,085 --> 00:09:02,059
"She is beautiful,
therefore to be wooed"

162
00:09:02,059 --> 00:09:06,451
"she is a woman,
therefore to be won."

163
00:09:06,451 --> 00:09:08,605
Henry the Sixth.

164
00:09:08,605 --> 00:09:11,609
- Are you hitting on me, Seth?
- Yes.

165
00:09:11,609 --> 00:09:13,983
Well, don't.

166
00:09:17,042 --> 00:09:19,342
He take the hint, stay away?

167
00:09:19,342 --> 00:09:23,137
Asked me to marry him,
few months after Grant died.

168
00:09:23,137 --> 00:09:25,822
Guess that'd be a no.

169
00:09:26,373 --> 00:09:31,743
Kinda had the fever for
Anne Bowen, huh, Dr. Garvey?

170
00:09:31,743 --> 00:09:33,569
No kinda about it.

171
00:09:33,569 --> 00:09:36,169
Didn't matter, she was
married to a fellow doc?

172
00:09:36,169 --> 00:09:38,230
Not saying I was proud of it.

173
00:09:38,230 --> 00:09:40,775
But the heart is a lonely hunter.

174
00:09:40,775 --> 00:09:43,100
Were you lonely enough to try
and get rid of Grant?

175
00:09:43,100 --> 00:09:45,103
Whoa, whoa.

176
00:09:45,103 --> 00:09:47,933
- Left field.
- New angle on his murder.

177
00:09:47,933 --> 00:09:51,422
He was shot by someone he knew.
From your hospital.

178
00:09:51,422 --> 00:09:53,561
You think I killed him
so that I could be with Anne?

179
00:09:53,561 --> 00:09:56,134
- Did you?
- That's crazy.

180
00:09:56,134 --> 00:09:59,084
Not really, happens all the time.

181
00:09:59,084 --> 00:10:02,587
All right, look,
I admit I was jealous of Grant.

182
00:10:02,587 --> 00:10:05,444
He was one of these guys that had it all.

183
00:10:05,444 --> 00:10:08,727
- But then he started falling apart.
- What was going on?

184
00:10:08,727 --> 00:10:10,688
His past was catching up to him.

185
00:10:10,688 --> 00:10:13,995
- Specifically?
- His genetic past.

186
00:10:13,995 --> 00:10:17,343
- Like his dad, he was an addict.
- Drugs?

187
00:10:17,343 --> 00:10:21,526
Cards.
Got the bug in Atlantic city.

188
00:10:21,526 --> 00:10:25,198
Then we went to a local game
near the hospital.

189
00:10:27,674 --> 00:10:30,933
- Last hand.
- You said that two hours ago.

190
00:10:30,933 --> 00:10:35,251
- Gonna get lucky this time.
- Said that two hours ago, too.

191
00:10:38,375 --> 00:10:40,103
Crap.

192
00:10:40,551 --> 00:10:43,215
Let me make a call.

193
00:10:44,735 --> 00:10:47,582
- Got a lie cooked up, doc?
- A lie?

194
00:10:47,582 --> 00:10:50,305
Car trouble.
Friend in need.

195
00:10:50,305 --> 00:10:51,952
Why don't you just go home to her?

196
00:10:51,952 --> 00:10:54,035
Or considering that you're a doc, though,

197
00:10:54,035 --> 00:10:56,266
I'd go with a pileup on the expressway.

198
00:10:56,266 --> 00:10:58,812
Lot of casualties.

199
00:11:02,671 --> 00:11:08,635
Hey, I'm so sorry.
Yeah, I know.

200
00:11:08,635 --> 00:11:14,234
Maybe half an hour.
It's been so busy down here.

201
00:11:18,320 --> 00:11:23,494
Actually, there was a pileup 
on the expressway.

202
00:11:23,494 --> 00:11:27,610
Yeah. Terrible.
Maybe an hour more.

203
00:11:27,610 --> 00:11:31,266
Okay. 
Bye, honey.

204
00:11:34,374 --> 00:11:36,890
That's the spirit.

205
00:11:39,999 --> 00:11:45,354
- I'm putting everything in.
- Whoa, doc, that's a lot of money.

206
00:11:45,354 --> 00:11:48,484
- You sure about that?
- Nothing's sure.

207
00:11:48,484 --> 00:11:51,489
That's what so great.

208
00:11:55,996 --> 00:11:58,757
You bluffing me?

209
00:12:10,370 --> 00:12:13,383
That doesn't cover it.

210
00:12:15,438 --> 00:12:18,644
Then I'll throw in my wedding ring.

211
00:12:19,546 --> 00:12:25,555
- What do you say?
- See the river.

212
00:12:30,564 --> 00:12:35,596
Showtime, doc.
Pair of bullets.

213
00:12:44,632 --> 00:12:48,456
You bet everything
on a stinking pair of twos?

214
00:12:48,456 --> 00:12:51,788
- You lousy river rat.
- I knew my luck was turning.

215
00:12:51,788 --> 00:12:55,241
I'll take you down, doc.
Do you hear me?

216
00:12:55,241 --> 00:12:57,887
You're going down!

217
00:12:59,340 --> 00:13:04,064
- Who was this guy lost his wedding ring?
- Cy Tisdale.

218
00:13:04,064 --> 00:13:07,002
He hung around the hospital,
getting paid to be in medical trials.

219
00:13:07,002 --> 00:13:08,337
Think he was dangerous?

220
00:13:08,337 --> 00:13:10,920
He had a pretty shady existence,
degenerate gambler.

221
00:13:10,920 --> 00:13:12,730
Which takes money.

222
00:13:12,730 --> 00:13:18,678
Money a rich doc like Grant had, 
and Cy needed.

223
00:13:30,698 --> 00:13:32,467
Anna Kournikova.

224
00:13:32,467 --> 00:13:34,249
What's that?

225
00:13:34,249 --> 00:13:38,322
Ace, king.
Looks good but never wins.

226
00:13:38,322 --> 00:13:40,826
You guys want in?

227
00:13:44,214 --> 00:13:46,649
- Like a bunch of roaches.
- Where are you going?

228
00:13:46,649 --> 00:13:48,973
I ain't the ringleader here.
Why are you pick on me?

229
00:13:48,973 --> 00:13:51,643
'Cause you knew Grant Bowen.

230
00:13:52,176 --> 00:13:55,663
True. Okay?

231
00:13:55,663 --> 00:13:58,863
He was shot, not long after you
made a threat against him.

232
00:13:58,863 --> 00:14:02,058
Said you'd take him down,
so maybe you did.

233
00:14:02,058 --> 00:14:06,317
Aw, that was just card talk.

234
00:14:06,317 --> 00:14:08,922
- Besides, a mugger killed him.
- No.

235
00:14:08,922 --> 00:14:11,838
New witness says it was a guy
in a st. Walt's baseball cap.

236
00:14:11,838 --> 00:14:15,707
Like the one you took
right of of Grant's head. / Nah, I...

